directory: crates/ctx-access
summary: Delivers the `ctx-access` binary and its backing library: the sole sanctioned path for agents to read and write source files under enforcement. Exposes init-task/read/write/list/end-task operations gated by access control, per-task caching, and chain-ordered context delivery. All real I/O is isolated behind the `Env` seam; the integration test suite exercises the full enforcement surface against an in-memory fake.
children:
  - src: Library and binary implementation — enforcement logic, CLI dispatch, and all supporting modules.
  - tests: Hermetic integration tests covering the complete enforcement contract via `FakeEnv`.
key_invariants:
  - write() requires a prior non-shallow read of the same target within the task; list() requires the directory's rollup.ctx to have been served first.
  - All paths are validated through `RepoPath::parse` at entry; no path can escape the repository root.
  - Access gate decisions are fully delegated to `ctx_core`; no local deny rules exist in this crate.
  - No code below `cli.rs` touches the process boundary; all filesystem and clock I/O is injected via `Env`.